NUMBER 3502
NAME Daerik Steel, Entryway
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
A corridor leads south from this place, perfectly straight as it enters the
heart of the complex. Its walls are lined with simple display screens, each one
bathed in the light of the one opposite it as images flicker and move. The
floor is a grillwork of black-painted steel, rattling slightly at the slightest
shift of your weight, and beneath it you can see faint glints of light from
metal wires and polished surfaces. The door to the decontamination chamber
is set into the east wall at this end of the passage.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 3503
; door to 3501 (decon chamber)
ITEM 0 943 VAL2=3501
; machine
ITEM 1 853
IFPREVERB OPEN 0
  CLEARVERB
  CLOSE 0
  ECHO PLAYER You realize that this is an automatic door which will open as soon as you try to walk through it.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  OPEN 0
  ECHO ALL The door slides open with a loud, "CLANK!"
  AFFECT 3501
  ECHO OTHERS The door slides open just long enough to let someone in.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell metal, like armor after a rainstorm.
  IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
    ECHO PLAYER Underneath this your wolfish senses detect something foul and rotten.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear clanking sounds down the corridor to the south.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3503
NAME Daerik Steel, Refinery
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand at the northwest corner of a vast, open chamber. The other corners
are at least a hundred paces away and the ceiling is over forty feet high, yet
no pillars or other supports are in evidence. Most of the floor space in the
immediate vicinity is taken up by a cylindrical machine of great size, rising
towards the girders above like a fortified tower. Some rubble is scattered
about, pieces of the walls where sections have broken up with the passage
of the centuries, much of it clustered at the base of some sort of lighted
console set into the huge machine.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 3504
EXIT SE 3506
EXIT S 3505
EXIT N 3502
; machine
ITEM 0 853 ADJ1=81 ADJ2=328
; panel
ITEM 1 282
; console
ITEM 2 718
; rubble
ITEM 3 213 VAL2=3504
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The side has been torn open to reveal several metal panels placed along the cylinder's radius.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER Each of the metal panels has several small slits in its side and the phrase, "Lael Contracting" inscribed proudly on its face.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK 2
  CLEARVERB
  RANDOM DUMMY1 1 12 0
  ; [1-10 can, of course, be expanded...]
  ECHO PLAYER Several paragraphs of text are repeatedly scrolling by on the console. You are
  ECHO PLAYER able to make out only a small portion:%c
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER     Log entry 4404: System Shutdown for routine maintenance. Able to
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER     bring about close in acceptable time. Will be bringing in
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER     both specialists have reported clear for 15:00 hours. Commencing
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
    ECHO PLAYER     Log entry 4416: Drilling cycle 1104 begun as scheduled. Latches 5
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 4
    ECHO PLAYER     Log entry 4425: Workers sent home for end of the world. No more
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 5
    ECHO PLAYER     regulations! Never liked this job anyway. Rorin help us all.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 6
    ECHO PLAYER     Log entry 4426: Final entry. It's really here. I felt the shockwave
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 7
    ECHO PLAYER     run through the ground a few minutes ago and all the electronics are
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 8
    ECHO PLAYER     failing, one by one. This computer will probably go next. I am going
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 9
    ECHO PLAYER     stay here and end it all. There's nothing left to live for.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 10
    ECHO PLAYER     Log entry 3220: Peterson called in sick today; we've all been working
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 11
    ECHO PLAYER     hard to keep up the pace without him. His lung replacement surgery
  ENDIF
  IFVAR DUMMY1 = 12
    ECHO PLAYER     should be completed by this time tomorrow and he expect to be on the
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 3
  IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
    ECHO PLAYER You climb to the top of the rubble and look down at everyone else.
    ECHO OTHERS %N climbs to the top of the rubble and looks down at you.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You climb to the top of the rubble and look around.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell the dusty air and try hard not to sneeze.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The faint humming sound you hear seems to be coming from the console at the base of the huge machine.
ENDIF
