IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The images painted into the glass seem to represent a streak of murderous black insect or, perhaps, a trail of black gases, bringing death to the unwary chalsuk.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  IFVAR RAC < 7
    ECHO PLAYER You fall to your knees in disgust, retching.
    ECHO OTHERS %N falls to %h knees.
    ECHO OTHERS %N retches.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 2
    POSITION KNEEL
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3509
NAME Daerik Steel, Machine Interior
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
This corridor comes to an end most abruptly, forming a rounded indentation in
the floor which appears to be used as a sleeping-place. Wads of bedding, torn
and shredded rags and plant fibers form a filthy mass with as much chalsuk hair
worked into it as anything else. From the stink of rodent sweat you can tell
that the bedding has been used in the immediate past.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 116
EXIT SW 3508
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You feel a little silly, inhaling this loathsome scent.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear scrabbling sounds all around you.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3510
NAME Daerik Steel, Machine Interior
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The passage through the unworked iron twists abruptly here as it plunges more
sharply downwards. A landing is formed by its sudden change of orientation, one
large enough to lie down on without rolling in the direction of the slope. From
the smell and the shredded condition of the rags and other trash gathered here
it seems that the chalsuk often sleep here in relative comfort.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3508
MONSTER_GROUP 116
EXIT SW 3512
EXIT E 3513
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER It smells so disgusting that your mind nearly shuts down in denial.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3511
NAME Daerik Steel, Machine Interior
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
Ending at a rough wall of gnawed and half-melted iron, the corridor seems
unfinished in this direction. Doubtless the work of the chalsuk will eventually
lengthen it, but from what you have seen of their digging ability it may well
be years before the passage goes even another ten paces.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 116
EXIT NE 3508
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell chalsuk sweat and garbage.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3512
NAME Daerik Steel, Machine Interior
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The walls around you are not of iron anymore, the metal having given way to
simple packed earth. This seems to be the repository for wastes and garbage
among the chalsuk. Thanks to their habit of scavenging things that other
species consider disgusting and worthless, of course, only the truly repulsive
ever makes its way into disuse. A slightly soupy mass of mold squishes under
your feet, sending unknown fumes wafting through the air.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 116
EXIT NE 3510
IFVERB SMELL -1
  IFVAR RAC > 6
    ECHO PLAYER You're glad that you're not organic, that's for sure.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR RAC < 7
    ECHO PLAYER The smell causes your mind to literally shut down for a moment.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gets an odd look on %h face.
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 6
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You realize that you've been babbling incoherently.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3513
NAME Daerik Steel, Machine Interior
INDOOR_FLOOR
MONSTER_GROUP 116
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
Dripping moisture has turned the end of this passage into a wall of brown and
red rust, a crumbling facade the color of blood. Flakes fall from ceiling to
floor even as you watch, a gradual process of "decay" which may well be faster
than the speed with which the weak chalsuk of these tunnels can dig them.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 3510
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You realize that inhaling rust is not a good idea.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear the snarling and rustling of chalsuk movements elsewhere in the machine.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3514
NAME Daerik Steel, Corridor
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
A simple corridor, lined with windows, leads south from the doorway here. Hints
and echoes of sound reverberate along its length, bouncing from the steel grids
which make up the floor and the ancient, unbreakable glass of the walls.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 3515
; door out
ITEM 0 943 VAL2=3506 UNLOCKED OPEN
IFPREVERB CLOSE 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The door is rusted open.
ENDIF
; window
ITEM 1 249
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFFULLDESC -1
    ECHO PLAYER [Daerik Steel, Office]
    ECHO PLAYER A small office greets your gaze, still faintly lit by the remains of its
    ECHO PLAYER lighting system. A desk and chair occupy most of the cubicle, joined only
    ECHO PLAYER by their sole occupant, a female figure slumped across the desk's blotter.
    ECHO PLAYER from the exposed wiring in her open back she seems to be a defunct mechanoid
    ECHO PLAYER or other inorganic humanoid.
    ECHO PLAYER Obvious exits: none.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER [Daerik Steel, Office]
    ECHO PLAYER A figure sprawled backwards over her desk is here.
    ECHO PLAYER Obvious exits: none.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear a series of metallic clangs to the south, like the footsteps of an armored warrior.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3515
NAME Daerik Steel, Corridor
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The corridor ends at a wall of rubble here, twisted strips of metal and
chunks of shattered concrete, their former cohesion ruined at some point
in the last thousand years or more. Shards of glass glitter in the light,
seeming to wink at you like the eyes of a waiting predator.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3514
EXIT ABOVE 3516
; opening
ITEM 0 72 VAL2=3516
EXTEND 0 in the ceiling
; rubble
ITEM 1 213 VAL2=3516
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The rubble is made up of fused, formerly molten metal as it is mortar, stone and more intact metals.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB FLY -1
  ECHO PLAYER You eye the opening the ceiling above you.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG2 = 1119
    ECHO PLAYER You are already at the top.
  ELSE
    EQUAL FLAG2 1119
    ECHO PLAYER You climb to the top of the rubble.
    ECHO OTHERS %N climbs to the top of the rubble.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR FLAG2 ! 1119
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The opening is too far up for you to reach from here.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear metallic footsteps from above.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3516
NAME Ceiling Above Corridor
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a crawl space above the ceiling, surrounded by a network of thin
girders. The surface under your feet is sufficiently removed from that above
you to allow you to stand, although you must keep a hand free to maintain
your balance. The air is filled with warmth and your skin itches at the touch
of something else in it. It is too dark to see exactly what, though.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 3515
EXIT W 3517
IFVERB SMELL -1
  GMMSG %N just inhaled a little asbestos. Kill %i.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3517
NAME Ceiling Above Corridor
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
You can see a corridor beneath you and hear a clanging sound as well, a
ceaseless din like the tramp of a dozen warriors in plate armor. Listening
more closely you can detect a hissing sound as well, rising and falling
along with the footsteps.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 117
EXIT D 3518
EXIT E 3516
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You smell smoke.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER You hear nothing new.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3518
NAME Daerik Steel, Corridor
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
The corridor leads south from here, leading away from a door surrounded by
driplets and discoloration, apparently welded shut by great heat. The floor
is scarred and blasted, burned and pitted as though exposed to constant
punishment for an unknown period of time. An opening just above the sealed
door leads through the ceiling above.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MONSTER_GROUP 117
EXIT S 3519
; door
ITEM 0 943 VAL1=999 VAL2=3518 LOCKED CLOSED
; opening
ITEM 1 72 VAL2=3517
IFPREVERB OPEN 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER It seems to be fused shut.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3519
NAME Daerik Steel, Corridor
INDOOR_FLOOR
MONSTER_GROUP 117
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
A smell invades your nostrils, scorched metal and rust combining to make
your eyes water and your skin feel grimy and dry. Your throat feels more
and more parched as you strive to penetrate the smoke which hangs low in
the air, passing over a door and the blasted walls and floor.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 3518
EXIT S 3520
ITEM 0 943 VAL2=3522 CLOSED UNLOCKED
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The smoke nearly chokes you where you stand.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3520
NAME Daerik Steel, Corridor End
INDOOR_FLOOR
MONSTER_GROUP 117
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
Another door is set into the wall here at the south end of the corridor. Smoke
and tiny sparks fill your vision and your lungs as you draw breath, possibly
poisonous fumes rising to obscure all before you and lend an air of seeming
slowness to every movement. The experience, disturbing as it is, still fails
to disconcert you as much as the hideous clamor and cacophony emanating from
all directions, the hammering blows of steel limbs on stone walls.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; door
ITEM 0 943 VAL2=3521 CLOSED UNLOCKED
EXIT N 3519
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER You cough.
  ECHO OTHERS %N coughs.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER Your ears ring with the din.
ENDIF
;
